ny of Adventurers, Vol. II |location=Markham, Ontario |publisher=Viking, Penguin Books of Canada |date=1987 |isbn=978-0-6708-0967-7 |url=https://archive.org/details/caesarsofwildern00newm }}\n* {{cite book |last=Newman |first=Peter C. |title=Empire of the Bay: An Illustrated History of the Hudson's Bay Company |location=Markham, Ontario |publisher=Viking, Penguin Books of Canada |date=1989 |isbn=978-0-6708-2969-9 |url=https://archive.org/details/empireofbayillus00pete }}\n* {{cite book |last=Newman |first=Peter C. |title=Merchant Princes: Company of Adventurers, Vol. III |location=Markham, Ontario |publisher=Viking, Penguin Books of Canada |date=1991 |isbn=978-0-6708-4098-4 |url=https://archive.org/details/merchantprinces00newm }}\n* {{cite book |last=Newman |first=Peter C. |title=An Illustrated History of the Hudson's Bay Company (Previously published as Empire of the Bay) |location=Toronto |publisher=Penguin Canada/Madison Press |date=2002 |isbn=978-0-6708-2969-9 |url=https://archive.org/details/empireofbayillus00pete }}\n* {{cite book |last=Newman |first=Peter C. |title=Company of Adventurers: How the Hudson's Bay Empire Determined the Destiny of a Continent |location=Toronto |publisher=Penguin Canada |date=2005 |isbn=978-0-1430-5147-3}}\n* {{cite journal | last=Opp | first= James | title=Branding 'the Bay/la Baie': Corporate Identity, the Hudson's Bay Company, and the Burden of History in the 1960s. | journal=Canadian Historical Review | volume= 96 | issue=2 |year=2015 | pages= 223\u2013256 | doi=10.3138/chr.2675 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Reed |first=Charles B. |title=Masters of the Wilderness |date=1914 |publisher=Chicago Historical Society, University of Chicago Press |url=https://archive.org/details/mastersofwilder00reed}}\n* {{cite book |last=Rich |first=Edwin Ernest |title=The History of the Hudson's Bay Company, 1670 \u2013 1870 |volume=Volume I.: 1670\u20131763 |publisher=Hudson's Bay Record Society |date=1958}}\n* {{cite book |last=Rich |first=Edwin Ernest