p of the [[Greens/European Free Alliance]] in March.<ref name=\"EP\" /> \nIn the 2019 election the Galicians nationalists were allied with the electoral coalition [[Ahora Rep\u00fablicas]], which included ERC, EH Bildu and some other minor nationalist parties as well. The coalition obtained 3 seats, which will be held rotatively, with Ana Miranda set to hold a seat for the last 3.5 years of the Parliament.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Ana Miranda (politician)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Miranda Paz, Ana}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:MEPs for Spain 2009\u20132014]]\n[[Category:MEPs for Spain 2014\u20132019]]\n[[Category:People from Caldas (comarca)]]\n[[Category:Galician Nationalist Bloc MEPs]]\n[[Category:Europe of the Peoples\u2013Greens MEPs]]\n[[Category:Women MEPs for Spain]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish women politicians]]\n\n\n{{Spain-MEP-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Thoughtfortheday", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCareer in the European Parliament:party allegiance", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ana_Miranda_Paz"}
