/16/19 Tornado Event|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSLCH&e=201912182057|publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet|date=December 18, 2019|accessdate=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat1}} | EF1\n|SE of [[Vicksburg, Mississippi|Vicksburg]] to NW of [[Bolton, Mississippi|Bolton]]\n|[[Warren County, Mississippi|Warren]], [[Hinds County, Mississippi|Hinds]]\n|[[Mississippi|MS]]\n|{{Coord|32.2043|-90.7831|name=Vicksburg (Dec. 16, EF1)}}\n|17:48\u201318:24\n|{{convert|22.68|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|616|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Utility poles were snapped and trees were damaged. A substation and numerous homes suffered damage, some significantly due to fallen trees.\n|<ref name=\"1216JAN\" />\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat3}} | EF3\n|NW of [[Liberty, Mississippi|Liberty]] to W of [[Bogue_Chitto,_Lincoln_County,_Mississippi|Bogue Chitto]]\n|[[Amite County, Mississippi|Amite]], [[Lincoln County, Mississippi|Lincoln]]\n|[[Mississippi|MS]]\n|{{Coord|31.194|-90.8942|name=Amite City (Dec. 16, EF3)}}\n|20:30\u201321:20\n|{{convert|30.43|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|880|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A large and intense tornado impacted numerous homes, ripping the roofs off, destroying carports, and collapsing some exterior walls. A large, well-anchored manufactured home was obliterated. Its walls, floor, and roof were scattered far downstream, and multiple half-ton trucks and livestock trailers filled with thousands of pounds of tools were moved or flipped. Along the entirety of the path, numerous trees were snapped or uprooted.\n|<ref name=\"1216LIX\">{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in New Orleans, Louisiana|title=NWS Damage Survey for Tornadoes and Severe Weather 12/16/19|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSLIX&e=201912180032|publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet|date=December 18, 2019|accessdate=December 18, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"1216JAN\" />\n