uck was tossed about {{convert|30|yd|m|abbr=on}}. Numerous trees were snapped or uprooted, and multiple power poles were broken.\n|<ref name=\"1216JAN\" />\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat1}} | EF1\n|ESE of [[Cherokee, Alabama|Cherokee]]\n|[[Colbert County, Alabama|Colbert]]\n|[[Alabama|AL]]\n|{{Coord|34.7043|-87.8715|name=Cherokee (Dec. 16, EF1)}}\n|22:50\u201322:52\n|{{convert|0.68|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|75|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Some tree trunks were snapped.\n|<ref name=\"1216HUN\">{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Huntsville, Alabama|title=NWS Damage Survey for 12/16/2019 Tornado Event - Update #6|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSHUN&e=201912211847|publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet|date=December 20, 2019|accessdate=December 20, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat2}} | EF2\n|[[Colbert Heights, Alabama|Colbert Heights]]\n|[[Colbert County, Alabama|Colbert]]\n|[[Alabama|AL]]\n|{{Coord|34.64|-87.7331|name=Colbert Heights (Dec. 16, EF2)}}\n|22:52\u201323:01\n|{{convert|8.18|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|250|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Numerous trees were snapped or uprooted throughout Colbert Heights. Several sheds were heavily damaged. One home had its roof entirely removed, with bricks blown off its west-facing wall and windows shattered as well. Three other homes suffered extensive roof damage, and others still sustained at least minor damage. A camping trailer was overturned.\n|<ref name=\"1216HUN\" />\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|storm}} | EF0\n|W of [[Lawrenceburg, Tennessee|Lawrenceburg]]\n|[[Lawrence County, Tennessee|Lawrence]]\n|[[Tennessee|TN]]\n|{{Coord|35.269|-87.519|name=Lawrenceburg (Dec. 16, EF0)}}\n|22:55\u201322:59\n|{{convert|3.76|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|25|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|The front porch and a portion of the roof was ripped off one house, and its toilet was uplifted about {{convert|1|ft|m|abbr=on}} above the flooring. A second house had a large number of its shingles removed. A large farm outbuilding was collapsed and another outbuilding saw its roof damaged. Sporadic tree damage was observed.\n|<ref name=\"1216OHX\">{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Nashville, Tennessee|title=NWS Damage Survey for December 16, 2019 Tornado Event|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSOHX&e=202001092052|publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet|date=January 10, 2020|accessdate=January 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat1}} | EF1\n|NE of [[Columbia, Mississippi|Columbia]]\n|[[Marion County, Mississippi|Marion]]\n|[[Mississippi|MS]]\n|{{Coord|31.2824|-89.7682|name=Columbia (Dec. 16, EF1)}}\n|22:56\u201323:07\n|{{convert|6.21|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|440|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Trees were snapped and uprooted. A couple of sheds were collapsed and some shingles from ripped from a home as well.\n|<ref name=\"1216JAN\" />\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat2}} | EF2\n|S of [[Town Creek, Alabama|Town Creek]]\n|[[Lawrence County, Alabama|Lawrence]], [[Limestone County, Alabama|Limestone]]\n|[[Alabama|AL]]\n|{{Coord|34.6445|-87.4126|name=Town Creek (Dec. 16, EF2)}}\n|23:08\u201323:31\n|{{convert|18.58|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|370|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|2 deaths \u2013 A strong tornado significantly damaged several mobile homes. One double-wide mobile home was rolled off its plot and destroyed, resulting in two fatalities. Three injuries occurred among the damaged structures. Near the end of the tornado's path, a small mobile home was shifted slightly off its plot while a small and well-built block outbuilding was largely demolished. Trees were damaged along the entirety of the track.\n|<ref name=\"1216HUN\" />\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat3}} | EF3\n|[[Sumrall, Mississippi|Southern Sumrall]]\n|[[Lamar County, Mississippi|Lamar]], [[Covington County, Mississippi|Covington]]\n|[[Mississipp