 homes. Three different groups of chicken houses were heavily damaged or destroyed as the tornado continued northeastward. Southwest of Mize, a well-built house had its roof ripped off and a majority of its exterior walls collapsed. Two trucks were thrown {{convert|200|yd|m|abbr=on}} into a pasture, and a few ATVs were thrown considerable distances as well. Multiple structures and chicken houses were damaged to the north of town, and another well-built house lost its roof and one of its outer walls. A large shed was destroyed and a tractor and boat were tossed {{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on}}. Along the entirety of the path, trees and power lines were downed.\n|<ref name=\"1216JAN\" />\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat1}} | EF1\n|[[Joe Wheeler State Park]]\n|[[Lauderdale County, Alabama|Lauderdale]]\n|[[Alabama|AL]]\n|{{Coord|34.8017|-87.3322|name=Joe Wheeler State Park (Dec. 16, EF1)}}\n|23:20\u201323:24\n|{{convert|2.9|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|500|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Thousands of trees were either snapped or uprooted by a multiple-vortex tornado.\n|<ref name=\"1216HUN\" />\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat1}} | EF1\n|E of [[Athens, Alabama|Athens]]\n|[[Limestone County, Alabama|Limestone]]\n|[[Alabama|AL]]\n|{{Coord|34.6997|-87.1010|name=Athens (Dec. 16, EF1)}}\n|23:30\u201323:43\n|{{convert|9.47|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Tree trunks were snapped, and a home had most of its roof ripped off.\n|<ref name=\"1216HUN\" />\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|storm}} | EF0\n|E of [[Cornersville, Tennessee|Cornersville]]\n|[[Marshall County, Tennessee|Marshall]]\n|[[Tennessee|TN]]\n|{{Coord|35.361|-86.823|name=Cornersville (Dec. 16, EF0)}}\n|23:41\u201323:45\n|{{convert|3.45|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|An outbuilding was collapsed, numerous shingles were ripped from a house, the metal roofing and siding was removed from a metal carport, and trees were sporadically uprooted.