==\nUnited's first departure of the 2003\u201304 season was [[David Beckham]], who left Old Trafford after ten years with the ''Red Devils''. On 7 July, forward [[Danny Webber]] joined [[Watford F.C.|Watford]]. A month after Webber's departure, Argentinian midfielder, [[Juan Sebasti\u00e1n Ver\u00f3n]] joined United's rivals [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]. Two days later, English forward [[Jimmy Davis (footballer)|Jimmy Davis]] died in a car crash.\n\nComing in during the summer transfer window were French forward [[David Bellion]], Cameroonian midfielder [[Eric Djemba-Djemba]], American goalkeeper [[Tim Howard]], Brazilian midfielder [[Jos\u00e9 Kl\u00e9berson|Kl\u00e9berson]], and Portuguese winger [[Cristiano Ronaldo]].\n\nLeaving in the winter transfer window was [[Alan Tate (footballer)|Alan Tate]], who joined [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]]. First-choice goalkeeper [[Fabien Barthez]] rejoined [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] in April, while [[Danny Pugh]] joined [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] in late May, in exchange for [[Alan Smith (footballer, born 1980)|Alan Smith]].\n\nArriving in the winter transfer window was [[Louis Saha]], who signed from [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] on 23 January for a fee of \u00a312.82&nbsp;million. Alan Smith joined United on 26 May from Leeds United in exchange for Danny Pugh (see above). [[Gabriel Heinze]] joined United on 11 June from [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] for a fee of \u00a36.9&nbsp;million.\n\n===In===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Pos.\n!Name\n!From\n!Fee\n|-\n|1 July 2003\n|FW\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[David Bellion]]\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]]\n|\u00a32m<ref>{{cite news |title=Bellion to cost United at least \u00a32 million |url=http://menmedia.co.uk/manchestereveningnews/sport/football/manchester_united/s/70/70235_bellion_to_cost_united_at_least_2_million.html?order=replies&submit=Sort |work=Manchester Evening News |date=16 October 2003 |accessdate=8 February 2012}}</